column1: If you are in Dallas County and want to get tested for COVID-19 please visit https://t.co/6YjD4pNZ3R to find a testing location near you.

The Latino population is disproportionately affected by Covid-19. This new @pbs series highlights how Latino communities are fighting to protect themselves against the pandemic.  https://t.co/XQZwQrrZnv
With recent COVID-19 spikes and flu season in full swing make sure you and your loved ones #GetCovered! Visit here for info: https://t.co/G4WLyk5fMc https://t.co/ntuPkmGMdn

My annual job fair is taking place this Friday November 13th at 9:30 CT! It will be a bit different this year due to COVID-19 but we will still be helping our participants to get tips on interview practices resume writing and so much more!

#Covid19 has made it clearer than ever that everyone needs reliable high-speed broadband. Today the #TrumpFCC doubled down on repealing #NetNeutrality. If you agree that internet access should be a right not a privilege join us in fighting to restore a free & open internet. https://t.co/gV7zYhrzEb

Millions of Americans MUST work during the #COVID19 pandemic to feed their families.   See if you qualify for paid sick and family leave under the #FamiliesFirst Coronavirus Response Act.   Visit https://t.co/vnAZ2u1bXR for more information.   #KnowYourRights
Happening at 2:30 pm CT today! Join me on FB Live and get your questions answered regarding COVID updates and issues affecting the DFW Metroplex. https://t.co/WtJV2217cN

AT&T has cut about 40000 jobs during this pandemic. This week I wrote a letter to CEO of AT&T John T. Stankey and urged him to take the necessary steps to help our nation recover economically from the COVID-19 pandemic.   Read the full letter here⬇️ https://t.co/vGjpFRWktY

Tonight the House passed a huge COVID relief bill to:    ✔️Restore $600/week in unemployment    ✔️Help small businesses   ✔️Provide another round of stimulus checks    ✔️Help our airline workers   Read my full statement here: https://t.co/RbzvenYkry

This #LaborDay we remember all who have fought for workers’ rights from the shop floor in the streets and on the picket line.   House Democrats will always live by our commitment to fight for American workers--especially during this #COVID19 pandemic. https://t.co/VKyyXLOROO

Medicaid covers over 75 million people including 40% of children & nearly 2/3 of nursing home residents. Yet the GOP HEALS Act does nothing to strengthen what is a lifeline during the coronavirus pandemic. Any future relief bill MUST strengthen #Medicaid. #NoOneLeftBehind

ICYMI: This week I held a live telephone town hall meeting on topics that are impacting our Metroplex like COVID-19 relief and the 2020 Census count. You can listen to the full town hall by visiting:   https://t.co/L1B2MjVwug

Americans rely on internet for their jobs their health and their education. That is why I led a letter to House leadership urging them to bolster access to broadband in the next #COVID-19 relief bill. https://t.co/3BLGdHIDk7

COVID-19 has devastated the child care sector forcing closures and exacerbating the shortage of quality affordable care. Today I was proud to advance two bills to provide relief for families and providers and support the safe reopening of our economy. #SaveChildCare https://t.co/kvKYI4sOeZ

Scammers are taking advantage of the pandemic to prey on the financial and physical health of Americans. I am proud to be an original cosponsor of the Stopping COVID Scams Act of 2020—legislation that will protect consumers and help put an end to these harmful scams. https://t.co/tSNPwiBHZQ

Americans are suffering right now. Today I joined my fellow Texans @RepColinAllred @JacksonLeeTX18 and @RepEBJ on a call to demand that Senate Republicans stop playing politics and immediately extend emergency unemployment insurance amid the #COVID19 pandemic. https://t.co/1Lyg9fdaR9

#COVID19 has further revealed the digital divide in our country especially for students. Our students need internet access at home this fall. That’s exactly why my Democratic colleagues and I passed the #MovingForward Act to spend $5 billion to close the #homeworkgap. https://t.co/ReD94FUQht
May 15: 1449026 COVID-19 cases in the US Now: Roughly 3800000 US cases It’s been two months since the House passed the #HeroesAct – and STILL the Republican Senate continues to refuse to take action.

North Texas families shouldn’t have to choose between paying their energy bills or putting food on the table.  Proud to join a bipartisan group of my colleagues to introduce legislation that will helping working families afford their utility bills during the #COVID-19 pandemic.

This is heartbreaking news. My thoughts and prayers go out to @JoaquinCastrotx & @JulianCastro on the loss of their stepmother due to COVID-19. https://t.co/MUOTILlYxD

This Administration keeps putting politics over people's lives during the #COVID19 pandemic. Ignoring health experts and issuing their own guidelines is a dangerous decision that will put students parents and educators in harm's way.   https://t.co/0e4U8gFzcc

Proud that my colleagues in the Senate introduced legislation that parallels the Emergency Broadband Connections Act that I introduced in the House earlier this year. This legislation ensures that millions of Americans can access essential broadband services during #COVID19. https://t.co/RuSon710fW

Minorities older adults and under-served communities have been hit by the pandemic at an alarming rate. I teamed up with Dr. Garth Graham to discuss ways we could tackle health disparities so Black Hispanic Americans are impacted less by #COVID19. https://t.co/i8Y0XY7MGT

Inaction is unacceptable.   Thousands of Americans are sick and dying due to #COVID19.    We need to expand affordable health care not strip it away.    That is why we must pass the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Enhancement Act today. https://t.co/EqlhsrWeiw

That is why I joined my fellow Texans to urge Governor Abbott to enact a statewide mandate on common sense safety measures like this. It is time to stop playing politics and work together to slow the damage caused by this administration's inadequate #COVID19 response. (2/3)

Millions are unemployed. More than 120000 have lost their lives. And cases are climbing in Texas. The LAST thing we need right now is a testing slowdown. This administration’s effort to slow down coronavirus testing is a threat to Americans nationwide. https://t.co/hSOMACnjzP
